<exercise checkit-seed="0005" checkit-slug="AI5" checkit-title="Density, Mass, Centers of Mass">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Consider a pyramid  that has square base with side length 7 feet, and height 10 feet.  Suppose that at height <m>h</m> feet the density of this pyramid is <m>\delta(h)=\frac{27}{20} \, h + 2\ \text{kg}/\text{ ft }^3 </m>.
            
            <ol>
                <li>
                    Find an integral which computes the mass of this pyramid.
                </li>
                
                <li>
                    Find an expression involving integrals which computes the height of the center of mass for this pyramid.
                </li>
            
            </ol>
            
            
            
        </p>
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li><me>\int_{ 0 }^{ 10 } \left(\frac{49}{100} \, {\left(h - 10\right)}^{2}\right)\left(\frac{27}{20} \, h + 2\right) dh.</me></li>
            <li><me>\frac{\displaystyle\int_{ 0 }^{ 10 } h\left(\frac{49}{100} \, {\left(h - 10\right)}^{2}\right)\left(\frac{27}{20} \, h + 2\right) dh}{\displaystyle\int_{ 0 }^{ 10 } \left(\frac{49}{100} \, {\left(h - 10\right)}^{2}\right)\left(\frac{27}{20} \, h + 2\right) dh}.</me></li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
